Description: Fragment of oval handle of a pottery transport amphora at neck join, gradual curve. Clay medium, micaceous, red-brown. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: For a parallel see V. Grace, BCH Suppl. XIII 559. no. 24; she interprets the second letter as omega, but on neither piece is there a spur to the left. From the same die as 2011,5004.108. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0533)
